The term refers to the division of the
Balkan peninsula, formerly
ruled almost entirely by the Ottoman Empire, into a number of
smaller states between 1817 and 1912.
The Balkan Region
Balkanization
Why were the great powers interested in the
Balkan region ?
Interested in retaining great power status following
loss of territory and long slow decline. Internal
political problems weakened their ability to control
the region.
Interested in influencing the region to prevent Balkan
nationalism from destabalising their existing empire.
Nationalist movements threatened to spread within
their empire.
Defeat against Japan in 1905 and internal political
problems weakened this empire. Slav nationalism was
ecouraged by this empire. the region was also of major
strategic importance for them. Humiliation in 1908
increased their interest in the region.
This power had major irredentist claims in the
region, especially Trentino and Dalmatia.
